1
00:01:34,118 --> 00:01:37,118
[NARRATOR]
<i>As the fateful "Promised Day"
loomed over the new year,</i>

2
00:01:37,118 --> 00:01:40,218
<i>those who refused to become
victims of an unknown destiny</i>

3
00:01:40,218 --> 00:01:43,452
<i>began preparations
to alter the outcome.</i>

4
00:01:43,452 --> 00:01:46,052
<i>Their plans advanced
with the passage of time</i>

5
00:01:46,052 --> 00:01:48,118
<i>until spring was upon them.</i>

6
00:01:48,118 --> 00:01:52,218
<i>Ready or not, the "Promised
Day" would soon arrive.</i>

7
00:01:59,271 --> 00:02:00,595
[SHEEP BLEATING]

8
00:02:00,595 --> 00:02:01,636
That's a lot of sheep.

9
00:02:01,636 --> 00:02:02,867
[STATION ATTENDANT]
Oh, yes sir...

10
00:02:02,867 --> 00:02:05,967
It's our Resembool
Spring Sheep Festival.

11
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,900
Well, we're sorry
to interrupt...

12
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,033
We just need to
replenish our water.

13
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:12,933
Of course...
Please help yourselves.

14
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,967
Alright...
Unload the tanks.

15
00:02:14,967 --> 00:02:19,033
[SOLDIERS GRUNTING]

16
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:24,533
[CRATES THUD ONTO THE GROUND]

17
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:39,800
[MICK GRUNTS]

18
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,067
Doesn't look
like anyone's home.

19
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:44,067
We're here now,
Miss Winry.

20
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:46,567
[WINRY EXHALES HEAVILY]

21
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:50,633
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

22
00:02:56,233 --> 00:02:58,267
[DOOR CREAKS CLOSED]

23
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:01,233
Hmm... Still
smells like home.

24
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:07,433
[MICK]
Whoa.

25
00:03:07,433 --> 00:03:09,567
It's like an
automail bomb went off.

26
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:12,033
Try not to touch
the stuff in progress.

27
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:26,933
[WINRY]
It's gotten so
dusty in here.

28
00:03:30,733 --> 00:03:31,733
Hmm...?

29
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:35,133
[ED STAMMERS]

30
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:39,133
[WINRY SCREAMS]

31
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,600
[MICK AND LIAM GASP]

32
00:03:41,267 --> 00:03:42,800
Hey! What's
the matter here?!

33
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,867
[ED STAMMERS]

34
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:45,567
When did
Edward Elric get here?!

35
00:03:45,567 --> 00:03:46,233
[GUNS COCK]

36
00:03:46,233 --> 00:03:47,633
[DOG BARKS]

37
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,233
Drop your guns.

38
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:51,467
[DARIUS SCREAMS]

39
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:54,267
What the hell is
going on up here?

40
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:55,900
[WINRY]
Ling?

41
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:58,067
Wait... You guys are
Kimblee's men, aren't you?

42
00:03:58,067 --> 00:03:59,133
[DARIUS GRUNTS]

43
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:03,233
Hey, I know you guys.
You're from Briggs.

44
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:05,233
You two have been
following us this whole time?

45
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:06,833
[DOG BARKS]

46
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,733
[HEINKEL]
Everyone calm down!
Lower your guns.

47
00:04:08,733 --> 00:04:09,667
[WINRY]
Okay, Ed.

48
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:12,567
You wanna tell me
what's going on here?

49
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:14,833
Looks like a
cautionary tale about guns.

50
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:17,667
Don't be a smartass,
tell me why you're in my room.

51
00:04:17,667 --> 00:04:20,700
I just wanted someplace
private to eat my sandwich!

52
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,833
[DARIUS]
Whatever, just
put your guns down!

53
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:24,100
[LIAM]
Quit shouting at us!

54
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,033
[DOG BARKS]

55
00:04:25,033 --> 00:04:26,733
[MICK]
Will someone
shut that dog up?!

56
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,233
[DOG BARKS]

57
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:30,133
[WINRY]
Get out of my rooooom!

58
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:31,500
[MICK, DARIUS, LIAM,
AND HEINKEL YELL]

59
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:35,500
[WINRY BREATHES HEAVILY]

60
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,167
[WINRY GRUNTS ANGRILY]

61
00:04:36,167 --> 00:04:37,567
[ED STAMMERS]

62
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:42,567
[WINRY SLOWLY EXHALES]

63
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:44,567
[WINRY]
I was worried about you.

64
00:04:44,567 --> 00:04:48,100
[ED]
Uh...! Yeah... I was
worried about you too...

65
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:50,133
I thought Al
was with you.

66
00:04:50,133 --> 00:04:51,633
[WINRY GASPS]

67
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,200
He's at the train
station right now...

68
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:57,100
He's with Miles.

69
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,700
The train's
gonna leave soon.

70
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:00,967
You might be able to
make it if you hurry.

71
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:03,133
[ED BREATHES HEAVILY]

72
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,700
Hey, what's wrong?
Don't you wanna see him?

73
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,800
[METALLIC CLINKING]

74
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:16,233
Well, technically
I'm a fugitive right now...

75
00:05:16,233 --> 00:05:19,200
I can't risk
anyone seeing me.

76
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,700
But, still...

77
00:05:28,095 --> 00:05:33,286
[SHEEP BLEATING]

78
00:05:33,286 --> 00:05:34,798
The spring sheep festival...

79
00:05:34,798 --> 00:05:36,531
That takes me back.

80
00:05:38,398 --> 00:05:40,931
We'll be leaving
in just a minute.

81
00:05:40,931 --> 00:05:42,031
Okay.

82
00:05:44,798 --> 00:05:46,965
The next time you
see your home town,

83
00:05:46,965 --> 00:05:50,331
I hope that it's with
the eyes of your original body.

84
00:05:50,898 --> 00:05:51,998
Yeah.

85
00:05:51,998 --> 00:05:55,565
[METAL DOOR SLIDES CLOSED]

86
00:05:59,531 --> 00:06:02,898
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

87
00:06:07,665 --> 00:06:09,398
[PINAKO]
Winry?

88
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:15,731
Welcome home.

89
00:06:15,731 --> 00:06:18,765
Hey, Granny...
I hope you weren't worried.

90
00:06:18,765 --> 00:06:20,440
I missed you.

91
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,807
[PINAKO]
So who are these hooligans
you've brought with you?

92
00:06:24,807 --> 00:06:27,507
I'm really sorry about
all the chaos earlier...

93
00:06:27,507 --> 00:06:30,540
Liam and I are both
soldiers from Fort Briggs.

94
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:33,407
[LIAM]
We've been acting as
Miss Winry's bodyguards.

95
00:06:33,407 --> 00:06:34,407
Huh?

96
00:06:34,407 --> 00:06:36,707
Hey, Ling...
You remember me?

97
00:06:36,707 --> 00:06:39,873
What...? Oh, right...
I guess you know this guy.

98
00:06:39,873 --> 00:06:41,840
[WINRY EXHALES]

99
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:45,107
Heh... The name's Greed...
It's a pleasure to meet you.

100
00:06:45,107 --> 00:06:48,073
Uh... Huh?

101
00:06:49,107 --> 00:06:52,673
[EATING NOISES]

102
00:06:52,673 --> 00:06:54,073
[GREED]
And after all
that went down,

103
00:06:54,073 --> 00:06:56,540
these guys signed
up to work for me.

104
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:58,073
[WINRY]
Why did you
come to our house?

105
00:06:58,073 --> 00:06:59,040
We're trying
to get prepared...

106
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:01,973
His automail's in
serious need of maintenance.

107
00:07:01,973 --> 00:07:03,940
And I need him
in peak condition.

108
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:06,407
[PINAKO]
Give him
a look-see after dinner.

109
00:07:06,407 --> 00:07:08,907
It is your fine
craftsmanship after all...

110
00:07:08,907 --> 00:07:11,407
I'm not really
comfortable tinkering with it.

111
00:07:11,407 --> 00:07:12,107
Uh...

112
00:07:12,107 --> 00:07:13,573
[WINRY GRUNTS IN AGREEMENT]

113
00:07:13,675 --> 00:07:14,932
Yeah, of course.

114
00:07:21,412 --> 00:07:22,438
Ya don't say...

115
00:07:22,438 --> 00:07:25,371
Liore's getting up
and running again, huh...

116
00:07:25,371 --> 00:07:29,071
Good to hear... I was
nervous they might not.

117
00:07:31,505 --> 00:07:35,971
So... Why is Al traveling
with Major Miles anyway?

118
00:07:35,971 --> 00:07:37,971
[WINRY]
I'm not sure
on the details...

119
00:07:37,971 --> 00:07:40,405
but the Northern troops
are hatching some plan

120
00:07:40,405 --> 00:07:41,638
in the east...

121
00:07:41,638 --> 00:07:45,605
Al figured he could help out,
so he volunteered to tag along.

122
00:07:45,605 --> 00:07:47,405
I see.

123
00:07:47,405 --> 00:07:49,405
We ran into your
father in Liore.

124
00:07:49,405 --> 00:07:51,638
He should be on his
way to Central now.

125
00:07:51,638 --> 00:07:55,038
I think he's headed for
some slum named Kanama.

126
00:07:55,038 --> 00:07:57,671
You ought'a go there and
get the full story from him.

127
00:08:01,571 --> 00:08:04,638
You know... It's almost
The "Promised Day."

128
00:08:07,638 --> 00:08:10,505
Ling and Greed told
me all about it...

129
00:08:10,505 --> 00:08:13,138
It could give us the chance
to get our bodies back...

130
00:08:13,138 --> 00:08:14,938
but it's most
likely gonna result

131
00:08:14,938 --> 00:08:17,238
in catastrophe for Amestris.

132
00:08:20,605 --> 00:08:21,905
Listen...

133
00:08:22,971 --> 00:08:24,038
What is it?

134
00:08:24,705 --> 00:08:26,538
I want you to take
Granny and Den...

135
00:08:26,538 --> 00:08:28,038
...and leave
the countryfor a while.

136
00:08:28,038 --> 00:08:28,838
[WINRY GRUNTS ANGRILY]

137
00:08:28,838 --> 00:08:30,371
[WRENCH POUNDS
AGAINST ED'S FACE]

138
00:08:30,371 --> 00:08:31,605
I'm not running away!

139
00:08:31,605 --> 00:08:34,005
You can't just send
us off like that!

140
00:08:34,005 --> 00:08:35,171
I know you
wanna protect us,

141
00:08:35,171 --> 00:08:37,438
but you need to try
to save everyone!

142
00:08:37,438 --> 00:08:39,471
I'm gonna do everything
I can to stop it

143
00:08:39,471 --> 00:08:41,338
but there's a chance
it might not work!

144
00:08:41,338 --> 00:08:43,905
I don't wanna hear
any doubts from you!

145
00:08:44,505 --> 00:08:47,671
Please, Ed... You can't let
them go through with this.

146
00:08:47,671 --> 00:08:51,071
Just tell me you're gonna stop
them and save the country!

147
00:08:51,071 --> 00:08:53,338
I wanna hear you say that
you're gonna protect the country

148
00:08:53,338 --> 00:08:55,038
and then get
your bodies back...

149
00:08:55,038 --> 00:08:57,571
Do whatever it takes
to make that happen!

150
00:08:58,171 --> 00:09:02,038
[ED STAMMERS AND SIGHS]

151
00:09:04,371 --> 00:09:06,971
Winry... You make it
sound like it's easy.

152
00:09:06,971 --> 00:09:11,005
This isn't the time to
start doubting yourself, Ed!

153
00:09:11,005 --> 00:09:12,205
Listen to me!

154
00:09:12,205 --> 00:09:13,338
[ED GROWLS]

155
00:09:13,338 --> 00:09:16,005
Winry, you just don't know
when to shut up, do ya...?

156
00:09:16,005 --> 00:09:17,138
Edward!

157
00:09:22,671 --> 00:09:25,138
[GREED LAUGHS]

158
00:09:25,138 --> 00:09:27,538
Oh, man...
She's a peach.

159
00:09:27,538 --> 00:09:31,005
Sounds like she wants
everything... My kinda girl.

160
00:09:31,005 --> 00:09:32,538
That kind of wanting
is dangerous...

161
00:09:32,538 --> 00:09:35,938
It's not how reality
works... Take a look...

162
00:09:35,938 --> 00:09:38,671
This is what I got for wanting
something unrealistic.

163
00:09:38,671 --> 00:09:40,238
I disagree.

164
00:09:41,071 --> 00:09:43,505
You wanna bring back
someone that you've lost...

165
00:09:43,505 --> 00:09:46,305
You might want money...
Maybe you want women...

166
00:09:46,305 --> 00:09:49,205
Or... You might want
to protect the world...

167
00:09:49,205 --> 00:09:51,971
These are all common
things people want...

168
00:09:51,971 --> 00:09:54,605
Things that
their hearts desire.

169
00:09:54,605 --> 00:09:59,405
Greed may not be good...
but it's not so bad either.

170
00:09:59,405 --> 00:10:02,171
You humans think greed is
just for money and power,

171
00:10:02,171 --> 00:10:04,905
but everyone wants
something they don't have.

172
00:10:14,038 --> 00:10:16,105
[WINRY]
You're leaving in
the middle of the night?

173
00:10:16,105 --> 00:10:18,371
[ED]
We were actually planning
on leaving earlier today,

174
00:10:18,371 --> 00:10:21,138
but then we ran into you.

175
00:10:21,138 --> 00:10:22,971
It was good to see you...

176
00:10:22,971 --> 00:10:25,005
And thanks for
the tuneup, Winry.

177
00:10:25,005 --> 00:10:26,571
[ED LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

178
00:10:27,238 --> 00:10:29,005
[PINAKO]
If you happen to
run into Hohenheim,

179
00:10:29,005 --> 00:10:30,638
you make sure to
give him that message

180
00:10:30,638 --> 00:10:32,105
from your mother, all right?

181
00:10:32,105 --> 00:10:33,238
I will, I will.

182
00:10:33,238 --> 00:10:35,405
[WINRY]
Wait, Ed... I need to--

183
00:10:35,405 --> 00:10:38,205
Just lay low until
the Promised Day passes.

184
00:10:40,371 --> 00:10:42,405
We're gonna
stop them, Winry.

185
00:10:42,405 --> 00:10:45,271
And Al and I'll be home
before you know it...

186
00:10:45,271 --> 00:10:47,971
Have an apple pie
waiting for us, okay?

187
00:10:50,205 --> 00:10:52,038
[WINRY GRUNTS IN AGREEMENT]

188
00:11:00,205 --> 00:11:03,405
Man... That was
a serious day of labor.

189
00:11:03,405 --> 00:11:06,471
I can't help but feel like we're
wasting our time right now...

190
00:11:06,471 --> 00:11:09,138
We should be getting ready
for the Promised Day.

191
00:11:09,138 --> 00:11:13,605
By doing what...? We're still
waiting on Marcoh and Scar.

192
00:11:13,605 --> 00:11:17,038
[ZAMPANO]
Where the hell are they?
And what's taking them so long?

193
00:11:18,471 --> 00:11:20,171
[ZAMPANO SHOUTS]

194
00:11:20,171 --> 00:11:21,671
Doctor!

195
00:11:21,671 --> 00:11:23,271
Oh, it's you guys.

196
00:11:23,271 --> 00:11:25,538
Yeah, the guys who
you've kept here waiting!

197
00:11:25,538 --> 00:11:27,971
You wanna tell us
what took you so long?

198
00:11:28,438 --> 00:11:30,938
There's no time...

199
00:11:30,938 --> 00:11:33,171
We need to
get to Central.

200
00:11:35,638 --> 00:11:38,705
[GERSO]
You know... It's kind of
funny when you think about it.

201
00:11:38,705 --> 00:11:41,005
We're former
Amestrian soldiers...

202
00:11:41,005 --> 00:11:43,938
...and here we are, working
with an Ishvalan dissident.

203
00:11:43,938 --> 00:11:46,571
[ZAMPANO]
Yeah, I know...
We were born in Amestris

204
00:11:46,571 --> 00:11:49,271
so it makes sense that
we're trying to save it.

205
00:11:49,271 --> 00:11:50,705
I mean our families are here.

206
00:11:50,705 --> 00:11:54,138
[GERSO]
And while Scar has got every
reason to hate this country...

207
00:11:54,138 --> 00:11:56,338
Who'da guessed an
Ishvalan like him'd be here

208
00:11:56,338 --> 00:11:58,405
fighting to save it
right along with us.

209
00:11:58,405 --> 00:11:59,605
You've got it all wrong...

210
00:11:59,605 --> 00:12:03,571
I'm not trying to save your
country... I'm changing it.

211
00:12:05,571 --> 00:12:10,363
I want Amestris to acknowledge
what it did to my people...

212
00:12:10,363 --> 00:12:11,329
And I wanna make sure

213
00:12:11,329 --> 00:12:14,329
that it's incapable of
ever doing so again.

214
00:12:14,329 --> 00:12:16,763
[MASTER]
If you truly dream of
changing the world...

215
00:12:16,763 --> 00:12:19,329
you must first be able
to change yourself.

216
00:12:20,563 --> 00:12:23,729
The ebb and flow...
It's a simple rule of life.

217
00:12:23,729 --> 00:12:25,129
They're Ishvalan!

218
00:12:25,129 --> 00:12:26,463
But how?

219
00:12:26,463 --> 00:12:28,196
What took us so long...?

220
00:12:28,196 --> 00:12:31,363
As you can see, we've been
busy these past few months.

221
00:12:32,196 --> 00:12:35,263
These men have chosen
to join us as our allies.

222
00:12:49,163 --> 00:12:52,163
I look forward to
this every year... General.

223
00:12:53,429 --> 00:12:56,229
[GRUMMAN]
Well, I'm just happy we're
holding the drills on my turf

224
00:12:56,229 --> 00:12:57,696
for a change...

225
00:12:57,696 --> 00:13:01,463
It's too cold up north for my
men to have a fair fight.

226
00:13:05,496 --> 00:13:08,063
Everything is
set and ready to go.

227
00:13:08,063 --> 00:13:10,463
Everything's set
on our end as well.

228
00:13:10,463 --> 00:13:12,463
They've placed one
small stumbling stone

229
00:13:12,463 --> 00:13:13,729
in our path though.

230
00:13:13,729 --> 00:13:16,729
Hmm... What do
you mean, General?

231
00:13:19,563 --> 00:13:21,396
[GRUMMAN]
Well, it seems
Bradley himself

232
00:13:21,396 --> 00:13:23,729
has come to
observe the exercise.

233
00:13:23,729 --> 00:13:26,329
[MILES EXHALES FRUSTRATEDLY]

234
00:13:26,329 --> 00:13:29,029
[MILES]
The Promised Day is right
around the corner...

235
00:13:29,029 --> 00:13:31,563
I figured they would send
someone to keep an eye on us,

236
00:13:31,563 --> 00:13:33,729
but I wasn't expecting this.

237
00:13:35,229 --> 00:13:38,529
[GRUMMAN]
Oh well... we'll just have
to do something about it.

238
00:13:55,463 --> 00:13:57,063
[AL HEAVILY EXHALES]

239
00:13:57,063 --> 00:13:58,363
Not again.

240
00:14:02,763 --> 00:14:05,296
It's starting to happen
more frequently...

241
00:14:05,296 --> 00:14:08,063
and it's lasting
longer each time.

242
00:14:08,063 --> 00:14:09,463
We have to hurry...

243
00:14:09,463 --> 00:14:11,629
This bond isn't gonna
hold much longer.

244
00:14:11,629 --> 00:14:12,696
[LOUD THUD]

245
00:14:12,696 --> 00:14:13,963
[AL GASPS]

246
00:14:16,329 --> 00:14:20,429
[AL HEAVILY EXHALES]

247
00:14:20,429 --> 00:14:24,463
[SPLATTERING SOUNDS]

248
00:14:24,463 --> 00:14:26,129
[GLUTTONY]
I smell him!

249
00:14:26,129 --> 00:14:27,463
That's him alright...!

250
00:14:27,463 --> 00:14:29,496
I smell the Fullmetal
Alchemist's brother,

251
00:14:29,496 --> 00:14:31,129
the little armored boy!

252
00:14:31,129 --> 00:14:32,529
[AL GASPS]

253
00:14:32,529 --> 00:14:34,196
You want me to chase you?

254
00:14:34,196 --> 00:14:35,363
[GLUTTONY YELLS]

255
00:14:36,763 --> 00:14:37,896
[AL]
Not good!

256
00:14:37,896 --> 00:14:41,029
I can't fight him right now!
Not in this condition...!

257
00:14:41,029 --> 00:14:43,063
[AL BREATHES HEAVILY]

258
00:14:43,063 --> 00:14:45,163
[AL YELLS]

259
00:14:45,163 --> 00:14:46,363
[AL GASPS]

260
00:14:48,363 --> 00:14:53,363
[AL YELLING]

261
00:14:59,363 --> 00:15:02,363
What is this?!
What's happening?!

262
00:15:03,596 --> 00:15:04,629
[LOUD CLANG]

263
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:09,629
No... not now... Not now!

264
00:15:09,629 --> 00:15:11,496
[AL WHIMPERS]

265
00:15:11,496 --> 00:15:13,229
[LOUD THUD]

266
00:15:22,696 --> 00:15:24,463
You rest up, Alphonse...

267
00:15:24,463 --> 00:15:27,363
Just take it nice
and easy for a while.

268
00:15:27,363 --> 00:15:30,463
We'll wake you on
the Promised Day.

269
00:15:33,777 --> 00:15:35,777
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

270
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:40,560
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

271
00:15:48,502 --> 00:15:50,769
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

272
00:15:50,769 --> 00:15:53,402
Good evening...
Mind if I intrude?

273
00:15:54,436 --> 00:15:57,902
Hm... Just don't expect me
to offer tea or anything.

274
00:16:01,936 --> 00:16:03,002
[ROY]
Just to warn you...

275
00:16:03,002 --> 00:16:05,502
I'm gonna have time to take
you out to dinner soon.

276
00:16:05,502 --> 00:16:06,769
[OLIVIER]
So you're going
to follow through

277
00:16:06,769 --> 00:16:08,636
on your threat
after all, huh?

278
00:16:08,636 --> 00:16:10,269
[ROY LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

279
00:16:12,536 --> 00:16:15,369
I've gotta say...
Your mansion is enormous.

280
00:16:15,369 --> 00:16:18,402
Very fitting for
the Armstrong family...

281
00:16:18,402 --> 00:16:19,369
If you wanted to,

282
00:16:19,369 --> 00:16:22,202
you could hide an entire
battalion in there.

283
00:16:25,336 --> 00:16:28,169
You seem to be rather
enamored with it, Colonel.

284
00:16:28,169 --> 00:16:29,302
I'll leave it to you...

285
00:16:29,302 --> 00:16:31,469
...if something
happens to me that is.

286
00:16:31,469 --> 00:16:34,369
It's not like it'll
fit inside my casket.

287
00:16:35,302 --> 00:16:38,302
You mean you don't plan
on leaving it to your brother?

288
00:16:39,769 --> 00:16:41,669
If I had to decide
between the two of you,

289
00:16:41,669 --> 00:16:43,202
I'd rather you have it.

290
00:16:43,202 --> 00:16:45,369
Try not to take
that as a compliment.

291
00:16:45,369 --> 00:16:46,002
[ROY LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

292
00:16:46,002 --> 00:16:47,836
Nonetheless, I'm honored.

293
00:16:51,595 --> 00:16:52,691
[ROY]
I know it's a little late...

294
00:16:52,691 --> 00:16:56,491
...but congratulations on
heading the Armstrong family.

295
00:17:00,491 --> 00:17:02,291
They're hyacinths?

296
00:17:06,757 --> 00:17:10,291
" <i>Selim Bradley is</i>
a Homunculus"...?

297
00:17:11,757 --> 00:17:13,191
Y'know what
they represent...?

298
00:17:13,191 --> 00:17:15,491
Those hyacinths...
Know what they mean?

299
00:17:16,924 --> 00:17:18,491
I don't.

300
00:17:19,757 --> 00:17:21,724
They represent
ladylike charm.

301
00:17:21,724 --> 00:17:22,824
[OLIVIER GROWLS ANGRILY]

302
00:17:23,757 --> 00:17:25,224
[OLIVIER]
Get off my property!

303
00:17:25,224 --> 00:17:28,191
[ROY LAUGHS]

304
00:17:28,191 --> 00:17:31,357
[ROY]
Oh... I thought you'd
like them... So long.

305
00:17:32,791 --> 00:17:35,591
Tch... That little punk.

306
00:17:35,591 --> 00:17:42,757
[FIRE SMOLDERING
AND CANONS FIRING]

307
00:17:42,757 --> 00:17:46,857
[CANONS FIRING]

308
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:52,091
[GUNFIRE]

309
00:17:56,491 --> 00:17:59,657
[GRUMMAN]
This is beyond frustrating...
I feel so helpless...

310
00:17:59,657 --> 00:18:03,424
Why don't we just, accidentally
blow up the tower Bradley's in?

311
00:18:03,424 --> 00:18:05,157
Please don't
do that, sir.

312
00:18:05,157 --> 00:18:06,491
Major Miles, sir?

313
00:18:08,491 --> 00:18:11,591
[MILES]
So you haven't had any luck
locating Alphonse Elric?

314
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:13,357
[SOLDIER 6]
No sir, no one has...

315
00:18:13,357 --> 00:18:16,291
We're continuing to
search the area... but...

316
00:18:16,291 --> 00:18:18,324
Do you think they
might have caught him?

317
00:18:20,457 --> 00:18:23,824
The Promised Day is
tomorrow, so let's hope not.

318
00:18:24,557 --> 00:18:25,824
Uh, sir?

319
00:18:25,824 --> 00:18:26,791
Hmm...?

320
00:18:27,224 --> 00:18:29,224
General Hakuro is here.

321
00:18:29,857 --> 00:18:32,591
[HAKURO]
Your Excellency... I've come
here to give you a warning...

322
00:18:32,591 --> 00:18:33,591
General Grumman plans to--

323
00:18:33,591 --> 00:18:36,791
To use the Eastern
forces to stage a coup...?

324
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:39,591
I've anticipated the
General's next move.

325
00:18:39,591 --> 00:18:41,557
Actually... the threat
of a joint coup d'etat

326
00:18:41,557 --> 00:18:44,124
is just a decoy,
sir... A distraction.

327
00:18:44,124 --> 00:18:45,324
Their plan was
to draw the bulk

328
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:48,324
of the military's divisions and
attention away from Central.

329
00:18:48,324 --> 00:18:51,224
Ishvalan terrorists are
gathering to attack the city.

330
00:18:52,491 --> 00:18:54,524
Afterwards... General
Grumman will invade

331
00:18:54,524 --> 00:18:57,757
Central under the pretense
of stopping the terrorists.

332
00:18:57,757 --> 00:19:00,391
The General then plans to
ally with Colonel Mustang

333
00:19:00,391 --> 00:19:04,091
amidst the chaos in order to
take control of Central Command.

334
00:19:07,224 --> 00:19:09,757
[CANON FIRING]

335
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:15,557
[AIDE]
According to
the latest report,

336
00:19:15,557 --> 00:19:16,791
A large number of Ishvalans

337
00:19:16,791 --> 00:19:19,591
have been seen gathering in
the slums outside of Central,

338
00:19:19,591 --> 00:19:23,124
so we have evidence to support
General Hakuro's intelligence.

339
00:19:23,124 --> 00:19:24,691
[BRADLEY GRUNTS]

340
00:19:30,491 --> 00:19:32,624
Prepare the train
to depart for Central.

341
00:19:32,624 --> 00:19:34,591
I'm leaving you in command.

342
00:19:34,591 --> 00:19:35,757
[AIDE]
Yes, sir.

343
00:19:38,391 --> 00:19:40,657
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

344
00:19:41,757 --> 00:19:44,591
We should've known...
Mustang's treacherous.

345
00:19:44,591 --> 00:19:46,857
It wasn't enough to
strip him of his pawns...

346
00:19:46,857 --> 00:19:49,457
We should've put him
down in the first place.

347
00:19:51,657 --> 00:19:56,357
[TRAIN SCREECHING TO A HAULT]

348
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:02,424
We've stopped.

349
00:20:02,424 --> 00:20:03,824
What's going on here?

350
00:20:06,824 --> 00:20:08,324
[AIDE 2]
It's a herd of sheep.

351
00:20:08,324 --> 00:20:09,724
[AIDE 3]
We don't have time for this.

352
00:20:09,724 --> 00:20:11,491
[LOUD METAL CLANG]

353
00:20:17,391 --> 00:20:20,291
Hey... The engine just
started moving without us!

354
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:21,724
It did what?!

355
00:20:21,724 --> 00:20:24,657
[AIDE 3]
What the hell...?!
Hey...! Stop them!

356
00:20:24,657 --> 00:20:27,691
[LARGE EXPLOSION]

357
00:20:29,524 --> 00:20:31,257
[CONDUCTOR]
Heh...

358
00:20:42,657 --> 00:20:44,857
We've safely cleared the
sheep off the tracks...

359
00:20:44,857 --> 00:20:45,757
We're now heading for

360
00:20:45,757 --> 00:20:47,857
the rendezvous in
Central, as planned.

361
00:20:48,824 --> 00:20:51,191
Let's move out...!
The Colonel's waiting for us.

362
00:20:51,191 --> 00:20:52,591
[6 SOLDIERS]
Sir!

363
00:20:52,591 --> 00:20:55,191
[AIDE]
Damn it!

364
00:20:55,191 --> 00:20:56,624
[AIDE GROWLS IN FRUSTRATION

365
00:20:56,624 --> 00:20:58,757
You've been played
for a fool, General.

366
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:00,524
They set us up.

367
00:21:01,824 --> 00:21:03,824
They attacked
the Fuhrer's train.

368
00:21:03,824 --> 00:21:05,591
They blew it
up over a ravine!

369
00:21:05,591 --> 00:21:06,624
[HAKURO GASPS]

370
00:21:07,891 --> 00:21:10,157
[GRUMMAN LAUGHS]

371
00:21:15,891 --> 00:21:17,391
[GUN COCKS]

372
00:21:20,291 --> 00:21:23,191
[HAWKEYE]
This is it... Everything
goes down tomorrow...

373
00:21:23,191 --> 00:21:25,224
It's do or die now.

374
00:21:25,224 --> 00:21:27,657
I'm glad the two of
you've got my back.

375
00:21:27,657 --> 00:21:30,224
Hey, anything
for you, Riza...

376
00:21:30,224 --> 00:21:32,191
Even if it does
mean deserting.

377
00:21:32,191 --> 00:21:35,257
Aw, man...
There go our careers.

378
00:21:35,257 --> 00:21:36,224
[HAWKEYE LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

379
00:21:36,224 --> 00:21:37,857
Once the dust has settled...

380
00:21:37,857 --> 00:21:40,657
We'll make sure
the Colonel answers for us.

381
00:23:15,491 --> 00:23:16,857
The Fuhrer's dead?!

382
00:23:16,857 --> 00:23:19,357
He can't be dead!
This has got to be a mistake!

383
00:23:19,357 --> 00:23:21,791
We're still waiting on
confirmation that it's true.

384
00:23:21,791 --> 00:23:23,757
So have they even
started searching yet?

385
00:23:23,757 --> 00:23:25,357
[CREMIN]
Last I heard, they haven't...

386
00:23:25,357 --> 00:23:28,391
[OLIVIER THINKING]
They start panicking the moment
<i>they lose their leader...</i>

387
00:23:28,391 --> 00:23:30,391
<i>...like chickens
with their heads cut off.</i>

388
00:23:30,391 --> 00:23:32,291
[FRANK]
Gentlemen, this
is no time to fight!

389
00:23:32,291 --> 00:23:34,724
Our commander in chief
might very well be dead!

390
00:23:34,724 --> 00:23:35,691
[HARRIS]
We're aware of that!

391
00:23:35,691 --> 00:23:37,491
[OLIVIER THINKING]
<i>This could be my chance.</i>

392
00:23:37,491 --> 00:23:38,524
[OLIVIER GASPS]

393
00:23:42,357 --> 00:23:43,524
[EDDISON LAUGHS]

394
00:23:43,524 --> 00:23:48,124
[FRANK]
It's a genuine honor
to have you amongst us.

395
00:23:48,124 --> 00:23:50,691
Calm down...
Stop panicking.

396
00:23:55,557 --> 00:24:00,157
I'm still here with you...
And I'm watching over Central.

397
00:24:04,191 --> 00:24:06,324
[NARRATOR]
<i>Is it a demon
lurking in the darkness,</i>

398
00:24:06,324 --> 00:24:08,557
<i>or is it something
far more sinister</i>

399
00:24:08,557 --> 00:24:11,791
<i>hiding within the guiding
light you've always followed?</i>

400
00:24:11,791 --> 00:24:14,791
<i>The young man's only hope
is for a blast of black wind</i>

401
00:24:14,791 --> 00:24:18,291
<i>to separate him from
this unspeakable crisis.</i>

402
00:24:18,291 --> 00:24:21,391
<i>Next time on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood...</i>

403
00:24:21,391 --> 00:24:25,157
<i>...Episode 47:
Emissary of Darkness.</i>

404
00:24:26,157 --> 00:24:28,624
<i>Strike a light deep
within the heart of man</i>

405
00:24:28,624 --> 00:24:31,491
<i>in order to ward
away the darkness.</i>

